The paper deals with the problem of opportunistic spectrum access in cognitive radio networks, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms to optimize the use of available channels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
